        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — Paranursallia spinosa n. gen., n. sp., holotype MNHN.F.PSA214, skull, pectoral girdle and beginning of the axial skeleton. Abbreviations: AN, angular; ART, articular;CLT, cleithrum;DN, dentary;DPTE, dermopterotic;DSPH, dermosphenotic;ENPT, entopterygoid;FR, frontal;HCLT, hypercleithrum (= supracleithrum); HYOM + DHYOM, hyomandibula + dermhyomandibula;iorb. c., infraorbital sensory canal;METH, mesethmoid;MPT, metapterygoid;MX, maxilla;NSP 1-8, neural spines 1 to 8; PA, parietal;PFR, prefrontal;PMX, premaxilla;POP, preopercle;PART, prearticular;PS, parasphenoid;PT, posttemporal;SCB, scale bar; SCL, sclerotic bone; SCU I d., v., dorsal and ventral first scute; ST, supratemporal; SYN, synarcual (probably including the exocciptals); VO, vomer. Scale bar: 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4535090/files/figure.png" .

